---

## Core Components

### Server

The server creates the listening socket, accepts new client connections, monitors file descriptors, receives raw data, parses IRC commands, and sends responses.

### Client

The client object stores information about a connected user, including socket descriptor, nickname, username, authentication state, registration state, and joined channels.

### Channel

The channel object manages users, operators, topics, invitations, and channel modes.

### Command Handler

The command handler parses incoming messages and dispatches each IRC command to the correct execution logic.

