## What I Learned

Through this project, I practiced:

* TCP socket programming in C++
* Non-blocking I/O
* Event-driven server design
* IRC protocol basics
* Command parsing and validation
* Managing multiple clients simultaneously
* Designing server-side classes
* Handling network errors and disconnections
* Building a structured C++ project with Makefile

---

## Limitations

This project is an educational IRC server. It implements the required functionality for the 42 curriculum but does not aim to fully reproduce every detail of a production IRC daemon.

Possible missing or simplified features include:

* Full IRC RFC compliance
* TLS/SSL encryption
* Persistent server state
* Server-to-server communication
* Advanced IRC services

